> Since our spherical curve on the 4-sphere is the 
> image of a cubic Bezier under M, which is a Bezier
> curve of degree 6 (see yesterday's note), don't we
> get continuity for free using Bezier curve properties?
> On first blush, I don't think that continuity arguments
> would change in 4d.
> jj
> 

Yes, continuity is free.  We must, however, show that we
are not introducing cusps into the curve.  I do not think 
that we will, but I would like to prove it.

